# Lunar → Shopify Importer

A browser-based tool for importing Lunar Distribution shipment files into Shopify.

## Live App

Once GitHub Pages is enabled, your app will be at:

```
https://<your-username>.github.io/<repo-name>/
```

-----

## How to Deploy

### First time setup

1. Create a new repository on GitHub (public or private)
1. Upload all files from this folder to the repo
1. Go to **Settings → Pages**
1. Under **Source**, select **Deploy from a branch**
1. Select **main** branch and **/ (root)** folder
1. Click **Save**
1. Wait ~60 seconds, then visit your Pages URL

### Updating the app

Just replace `index.html` with the new version and push/upload to GitHub.
GitHub Pages will redeploy automatically within ~60 seconds.

-----

## How to Use

1. Open the app URL in any browser (desktop or iPhone Safari)
1. Click **Connect to Shopify** in the bottom status bar
1. Enter your `myshopify.com` domain and Admin API access token
1. Load your Lunar Distribution CSV shipment file
1. Preview → Review & Match → Push to Shopify

### Getting a Shopify Admin API Token

1. In Shopify Admin go to **Settings → Apps and sales channels**
1. Click **Develop apps** → **Create an app**
1. Name it (e.g. “Lunar Importer”)
1. Under **Configuration**, enable these Admin API scopes:
- `read_products`
- `write_products`
- `read_inventory`
- `write_inventory`
- `read_locations`
1. Click **Install app** → **Reveal token once**
1. Copy the token — starts with `shpat_`

> Tokens are entered per session and never stored by the app.

-----

## File Format

The app expects a Lunar Distribution CSV export with these columns:

|Column            |Used for                     |
|------------------|-----------------------------|
|`Code`            |Shopify SKU + cover image URL|
|`Title`           |Product title                |
|`Qty`             |Inventory quantity           |
|`Retail`          |Compare-at price             |
|`Discounted Price`|Selling price                |
|`UPC`             |Barcode                      |
|`In-Store Date`   |Display reference            |
|`Item Category`   |`1` = Comic, `0` = Promo     |

Cover images are loaded from:

```
https://media.lunardistribution.com/images/covers/{Code}.jpg
```

-----

## Notes

- No data is sent to any third party — all API calls go directly from your browser to Shopify
- Credentials are held in memory only, cleared when the tab is closed
- Promo items (Category 0 or $0.00) are flagged but not auto-selected — you can include them manually
- Inventory is set at your store’s first/primary location
